        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli-runner): return updatedInput for allowed Claude can_use_tool responses",
        "body": "### What Problem This Solves\n\nClaude Code 2.1.156 rejects the allow response OpenClaw sends for `can_use_tool` control requests because it still uses the deprecated `{ behavior: \"allow\" }` shape. Every tool call that goes through the permission/approval flow fails with a ZodError before the tool runs (see #95171).\n\n### Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe new Claude Code `PermissionResult` schema expects the allow branch to be `{ updatedInput: <input> }`. This change returns the original tool input back to Claude for allowed native tool calls, while keeping the existing deny branch unchanged.\n\n### User Impact\n\nUsers on Claude Code >= 2.1.156 can now use tools that hit the exec approval flow (e.g. `Bash`, `WebFetch`, `Grep` outside cwd) without getting a ZodError.\n\n### Evidence\n\nAdded `src/agents/cli-runner/claude-live-session.can-use-tool.test.ts`.\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/cli-runner/claude-live-session.can-use-tool.test.ts\n```\n\nResult: 2 tests passed.\n\nFixes #95171",
        "branch": "fix/95171-claude-can-use-tool-updated-input",
